<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='422000' id='t-422000'>(Laughter)</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 7:15
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='424000' id='t-424000'>So these questions ... what is happening in the world</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='426000' id='t-426000'>is the big stuff, actually,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='428000' id='t-428000'>is done magnificently well.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='430000' id='t-430000'>But the small stuff, what you might call the user interface,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='433000' id='t-433000'>is done spectacularly badly.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='435000' id='t-435000'>But also, there seems to be a complete sort of gridlock</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='438000' id='t-438000'>in terms of solving these small solutions.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='441000' id='t-441000'>Because the people who can actually solve them</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='443000' id='t-443000'>actually are too powerful and too preoccupied</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='445000' id='t-445000'>with something they think of as &quot;strategy&quot; to actually solve them.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='448000' id='t-448000'>I tried this exercise recently, talking about banking.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='450000' id='t-450000'>They said, &quot;Can we do an advertising campaign?</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='452000' id='t-452000'>What can we do and encourage more online banking?&quot;</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='455000' id='t-455000'>I said, &quot;It's really, really easy.&quot;</span>
