<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='513000' id='t-513000'>And yet, it never happens.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
 8:46
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='515000' id='t-515000'>Because there's a fundamental disconnect, as I said,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='518000' id='t-518000'>that actually, the people with the power</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='520000' id='t-520000'>want to do big expensive things.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='522000' id='t-522000'>And there's to some extent a big strategy myth</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='524000' id='t-524000'>that's prevalent in business now.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='526000' id='t-526000'>And if you think about it, it's very, very important</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='528000' id='t-528000'>that the strategy myth is maintained.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='530000' id='t-530000'>Because, if the board of directors convince everybody</span>
