<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='589000' id='t-589000'>very, very small changes</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='591000' id='t-591000'>can have disproportionately huge effects,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='593000' id='t-593000'>and equally, vast areas of activity, enormous mergers,</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='596000' id='t-596000'>can actually accomplish absolutely bugger-all.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='600000' id='t-600000'>But it's very, very uncomfortable for us</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='602000' id='t-602000'>to actually acknowledge that we're living in such a world.</span>
</span>
</p>
<p class='talk-transcript__para'>
<data class='talk-transcript__para__time'>
10:16
</data>
<span class='talk-transcript__para__text'>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='605000' id='t-605000'>But what I'm saying is we could just make things</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='607000' id='t-607000'>a little bit better for ourselves</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='609000' id='t-609000'>if we looked at it in this very simple four-way approach.</span>
<span class='talk-transcript__fragment' data-time='613000' id='t-613000'>That is actually strategy, and I'm not denying that strategy has a role.</span>
